157
00:11:50,976 --> 00:11:53,513
I realize now just how significant

158
00:11:55,415 --> 00:11:56,716
his presence was in my life.

159
00:12:02,555 --> 00:12:04,224
I think that for Shintaro-kun,

160
00:12:04,636 --> 00:12:08,127
your presence was the most significant.

161
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:12,298
Maybe.

162
00:12:14,272 --> 00:12:15,240
It's just that

163
00:12:15,959 --> 00:12:17,637
I'm the only one who forgot him.

164
00:12:22,574 --> 00:12:25,311
Memories of someone important

165
00:12:27,547 --> 00:12:28,839
should be stored safely

166
00:12:28,864 --> 00:12:30,544
in a precious drawer.

167
00:12:31,100 --> 00:12:32,619
Right now, it's just that

168
00:12:33,033 --> 00:12:35,521
the drawer seems to be locked.

169
00:12:41,408 --> 00:12:42,595
Akira-kun,

170
00:12:43,111 --> 00:12:45,148
please keep holding on to hope.

171
00:12:45,876 --> 00:12:47,200
I believe your feelings

172
00:12:47,621 --> 00:12:49,969
will reach Shintaro-kun.

173
00:13:06,567 --> 00:13:07,754
Sakuma-sensei!

174
00:13:09,191 --> 00:13:12,058
Oh, Shintaro-kun. Hello.

175
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:12,992
Hello.

176
00:13:14,486 --> 00:13:15,662
Sensei,

177
00:13:18,033 --> 00:13:19,283
what's your relationship

178
00:13:19,308 --> 00:13:20,588
with Minato-san?

179
00:13:21,234 --> 00:13:21,934
Huh?

180
00:13:21,958 --> 00:13:22,735
Well,

181
00:13:23,095 --> 00:13:25,672
you were talking so friendly earlier.

182
00:13:27,269 --> 00:13:28,637
I was just wondering

183
00:13:28,926 --> 00:13:30,710
what you think of Minato-san.

184
00:13:34,443 --> 00:13:35,615
I've been

185
00:13:35,639 --> 00:13:37,650
asked that question before.

186
00:13:37,674 --> 00:13:38,484
Oh?

187
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:41,172
Akira-kun is a remarkable student,

188
00:13:41,188 --> 00:13:42,006
you know.

189
00:13:42,030 --> 00:13:43,356
He was, he is,

190
00:13:43,637 --> 00:13:44,791
and he always will be.

191
00:13:50,195 --> 00:13:51,464
Why did I

192
00:13:52,096 --> 00:13:54,233
ask this question before?

193
00:13:55,197 --> 00:13:56,257
Umm...

194
00:13:56,578 --> 00:13:57,770
I don't know.

195
00:14:00,873 --> 00:14:01,841
But

196
00:14:02,513 --> 00:14:04,610
the Shintaro-kun I know

197
00:14:05,024 --> 00:14:07,780
has always talked about Akira-kun.

198
00:14:08,581 --> 00:14:10,083
Sometimes with excitement,

199
00:14:10,848 --> 00:14:13,419
and sometimes with a grumpy face.

200
00:14:49,630 --> 00:14:50,834
(To Minato-san, )

201
00:14:50,834 --> 00:14:52,058
To Minato-san,

202
00:14:52,276 --> 00:14:53,575
thank you for taking care of me

203
00:14:53,607 --> 00:14:54,690
during my hospitalization.

204
00:14:54,714 --> 00:14:55,964
As a token of my gratitude,

205
00:14:55,980 --> 00:14:56,818
I baked cookies.

206
00:14:56,842 --> 00:14:58,403
Please enjoy them.

207
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:21,120
They're sweet.

208
00:15:35,636 --> 00:15:36,602
Shintaro,

209
00:15:36,703 --> 00:15:37,620
are you okay?

210
00:15:37,644 --> 00:15:39,040
Are you pushing yourself too hard?

211
00:15:39,065 --> 00:15:40,662
I'm fine. Really.

212
00:15:40,780 --> 00:15:41,941
Okay,

213
00:15:42,145 --> 00:15:43,596
but it hasn't been long since

214
00:15:43,620 --> 00:15:44,924
you were discharged.

215
00:15:44,948 --> 00:15:46,245
Don't overexert yourself.

216
00:15:46,691 --> 00:15:47,513
Yes.

217
00:15:54,020 --> 00:15:55,054
By the way,

218
00:15:56,444 --> 00:15:58,090
do you know why I

219
00:15:58,216 --> 00:15:59,699
started working part-time?

220
00:16:00,238 --> 00:16:00,960
Huh?

221
00:16:01,557 --> 00:16:02,428
I

222
00:16:02,553 --> 00:16:05,031
remember that I started working in May,

223
00:16:05,437 --> 00:16:07,567
but I can't recall why I decided

224
00:16:07,793 --> 00:16:09,368
to take on a part-time job.

225
00:16:11,103 --> 00:16:12,605
Well...

226
00:16:13,214 --> 00:16:14,373
Do you know something?

227
00:16:18,678 --> 00:16:19,545
